Events.RelatedBody:
Issue [NuGet/Home#9821](https://github.com/NuGet/Home/issues/9821) changed the public API of `NuGet.CommandLine.XPlat` to `internal`. 

We use `NuGet.CommandLine.XPlat` to push packages to a company internal NuGet feed by a direct call of the executable:
```CSharp
private static bool PushPackage(string nupkgFile, string apiKey, string serverUrl, string timeout)
{
    var exitCode = Program.Main(new[] { "push", nupkgFile, "-k", apiKey, "-s", serverUrl, "-t", timeout });
    return exitCode == 0;
}
```
With the [introduced changes in v4.8.0](https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/nuget/release-notes/nuget-5.8) this call is not possible anymore. Since I cannot find I workaround to push NuGet packages without including NuGet.exe, I would like to request it as new feature.

